MASERU, Lesotho, January 19, 2023/APO Group/ -- 
                                                        
                            The Cooperation Council for the Arab States of the Gulf, also known as the Gulf Cooperation Council paid a courtesy call to his Majesty King Letsie III and the Prime minister, Mr Ntsokoane Samuel Matekane on Wednesday.



In an interview with the Publication, the Minister of Foreign affairs and International Relations Mr. Lejone Mpotjoane said the courtesy call by the Cooperation Council for the Arab States of the Gulf is a response to His Majesty’s call to Middle East Countries to come to Lesotho and strengthen relations.

"The Prime Minister during the meeting stated that his government is working tirelessly to implement production of goods in the country working in line with developed countries as this will help enhance the economy’’ he indicated.
                                Saudi Arabia is planning to host World Expo in 2030 and Lesotho is willing to support Saudi Arabia
                            

He said Saudi Arabia is planning to host World Expo in 2030 and Lesotho is willing to support Saudi Arabia.

Similarly, the Head of the Delegation, Ambassador Sultan AL Angari from Saudi Arabia, said it was his first visit to the Kingdom of Lesotho.  He said he was honoured to meet with both His Majesty and Prime Minister.

He highlighted that he had a productive meeting that will benefit both Lesotho and his countries, adding that this meeting will enhance the bilateral relations between the two parties.

He stressed that Saudi Arabia is willing to help Lesotho build infrastructure projects, adding that Lesotho has great potential.

He, therefore, wished Basotho a prosperous New year.

The gulf cooperation is a regional, intergovernmental, political, and economic union comprising Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, and the United Arab Emirates.